{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":726,"name":"","username":"Hevedy","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/7feea3/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-03-12T14:11:23.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eMigrate from Xml to custom or Json\u003cbr\u003e\nBecause Xml is hard to read and takes much time to load.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdea \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#1:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eCustom Script:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nLike in Id tech or Cube 2\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExample of Material:\u003cbr\u003e\nOld Snow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/Diff.xml\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/Snow.dds\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatSpecColor\" value=\"0.25 0.25 0.25 16\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNew Snow.mtr (MaTeRial .mtr)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e/*\nMultiline Comment\n*/\n//Line Comment\nMaterial Snow {\n   //Here add maps and types and def of map (collisions, twosided, impacts...)\n   Technique Techniques/Diff.tch\n   Diffusemap Textures/Snow.dds\n   Specularmap 0.25 0.25 0.25 16\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOld MatBody.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffNormalSpecAlphaMask.xml\" quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/Nyra/body_d.png\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;texture unit=\"normal\" name=\"Textures/Nyra/body_n.png\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;texture unit=\"specular\" name=\"Textures/Nyra/head_s.png\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"Textures/Nyra/reflect.png\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"UOffset\" value=\"1 0 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"VOffset\" value=\"0 1 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatDiffColor\" value=\"0.4 0.4 0.4 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatEmissiveColor\" value=\"0 0 0 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatEnvMapColor\" value=\"1 1 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatSpecColor\" value=\"0.5 0.5 0.5 384.314\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;cull value=\"ccw\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;shadowcull value=\"ccw\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;depthbias constant=\"0\" slopescaled=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNew MatBody.mtr\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eMaterial MatBody {\n   Technique Techniques/DiffNormalSpecAlphaMask.tch {\n      Quality 0\n      Loddistance 0\n   }\n   Diffusemap {\n      Map Textures/Nyra/body_d.png\n      Color 0.4 0.4 0.4 1\n   }\n   Normalmap Textures/Nyra/body_n.png\n   Specularmap {\n      Map Textures/Nyra/head_s.png\n      Color 0.5 0.5 0.5 384.314\n   }\n   Emissivemap 0 0 0 1\n   Environmentmap {\n      Map Textures/Nyra/reflect.png\n      Color 1 1 1\n   }\n   UOffset 1 0 0 0\n   VOffset 0 1 0 0\n   Cull_0\n   Shadowcull_0\n   Depthbias {\n      Constant 0\n      Slopescaled 0\n   }\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdea \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#2:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eUse Json\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:20.454Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":20,"reads":12,"readers_count":11,"score":102.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":732,"name":"","username":"aster2013","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/aster2013/{size}/828_2.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T08:24:37.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCurrently, we use Pugixml, if you fell is slow on loading, You can replace it with RapidXml (\u003ca href=\"http://rapidxml.sourceforge.net/\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://rapidxml.sourceforge.net/\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut as I know, C++ Json parser is slower than xml parser,  the fastest Json parser call RapidJson (\u003ca href=\"https://code.google.com/p/rapidjson/\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://code.google.com/p/rapidjson/\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:20.892Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://rapidxml.sourceforge.net/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"RapidXml","clicks":1},{"url":"https://code.google.com/p/rapidjson/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Google Code Archive - Long-term storage for Google Code Project Hosting.","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":11,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":733,"name":"Yao Wei Tjong","username":"weitjong","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/{size}/4_2.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T09:20:59.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eDon‚Äôt forget we use pugixml library not only for its XML parser but also for its XPath implementation. So, any replacement should address for both needs. Although there are XPath equivalent implementation for JSON, there is no standard at all unlike XPath. Urho3D uses XPath query in a few places. IMHO, we should focus our energy on other area than this.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:20.991Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"Yao Wei Tjong","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Admin","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":4,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":734,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T10:02:36.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhen I profiled scene and XML loading, the most significant CPU hotspot I remember was the parsing of floats from string data, for example Vector3‚Äôs. Moving away from XML would not change this. Rather, large data files like scenes / object prefabs should be binary in a final production.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:21.066Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":735,"name":"","username":"Hevedy","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/7feea3/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T11:19:06.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/40/3_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e cadaver:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen I profiled scene and XML loading, the most significant CPU hotspot I remember was the parsing of floats from string data, for example Vector3‚Äôs. Moving away from XML would not change this. Rather, large data files like scenes / object prefabs should be binary in a final production.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHow you profile? What use ?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:21.128Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":736,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T12:28:07.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAMD CodeAnalyst.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:21.195Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":739,"name":"","username":"Hevedy","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/7feea3/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T14:12:51.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/40/3_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e cadaver:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAMD CodeAnalyst.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWork that with Intel/Nvidia ?\u003cbr\u003e\nI think would be nice add to the engine some debug/profiler like this \u003ca href=\"http://freesdk.crydev.net/display/SDKDOC2/Debugging+and+Profiling+Tools\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003efreesdk.crydev.net/display/SDKDO ‚Ä¶ ling+Tools\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTy.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:21.429Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://freesdk.crydev.net/display/SDKDOC2/Debugging+and+Profiling+Tools","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":740,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2014-03-13T14:21:36.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCodeAnalyst works with Intel CPU‚Äôs in a limited fashion. You can get the percentage of time spent in parts of code, which is often the most important knowledge. On AMD CPU‚Äôs it also shows hardware counters like cache misses etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUrho3D already has its own hierarchic execution time profiler, which is already used quite extensively in the engine (F2 to show it in the examples). In addition there are some additional profiling/dumping functions in Engine class, but they‚Äôre not always usable, for example the memory allocation dump works only in MSVC debug mode.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTotal rewrite of memory allocations to always go through a custom memory allocation profiler is not planned.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:21.519Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1139,"name":"","username":"aster2013","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/aster2013/{size}/828_2.png","created_at":"2014-04-18T06:18:01.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI will add JSON support before next release. But I don‚Äôt want to replace current xml data file. If you like, you can use JSON for your custom data file.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:58:52.109Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":1.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":11,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1366,"name":"","username":"Hevedy","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/7feea3/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-05-14T19:21:37.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/aster2013/40/828_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e aster2013:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI will add JSON support before next release. But I don‚Äôt want to replace current xml data file. If you like, you can use JSON for your custom data file.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOh nice thanks. But is ready to read the materials and others ?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:09.465Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":1.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1509,"name":"","username":"OvermindDL1","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/o/a8b319/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-05-26T01:08:38.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am unsure if a C++ lib exists for it, but I would recommend hocon over JSON.  It is a strict superset of JSON, but allows for includes, more readable formatting, comments, etc.  The ‚Äòspec‚Äô, is at \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/typesafehub/config/blob/master/HOCON.md\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com/typesafehub/config/b ‚Ä¶ r/HOCON.md\u003c/a\u003e and it is very much used in the java world now at least, it is definitely superior to JSON while being a strict superset, thus JSON works as-is with it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSomething that is not JSON based but is very powerful, very fast, easy, succinct, type safe(woo!) with many useful features (including comments) that is a C++ lib is:  \u003ca href=\"http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehyperrealm.com/libconfig/\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nIt is lgpl thankfully.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:21.089Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":1.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/typesafehub/config/blob/master/HOCON.md","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"config/HOCON.md at master ¬∑ typesafehub/config ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"libconfig - C/C++ Configuration File Library","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":42,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":1520,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2014-05-27T11:40:50.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLGPL libraries are not OK for Urho3D, as we need to be able to compile into static libraries on iOS, and embed into .apk‚Äôs on Android, and both scenarios don‚Äôt readily allow the user to replace the library in question. We can take only permissive licenses with no restriction on static linking (BSD/MIT/Apache etc.)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T00:59:21.911Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":141,"topic_slug":"migrate-from-xml-to-custom-or-json","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":nul